headline: Hewlett Packard Enterprise beats quarterly results estimates on strong AI server demand
summary: Demand for HPE's servers, equipped with Nvidia processors, has remained healthy as enterprises invest heavily in hardware that can support and process the swathes of data used in training AI models.  Despite a weaker performance, HPE has been seeing an improvement in its Intelligent Edge business, which provides networking hardware such as switches and Wi-Fi access points.  Intelligent Edge revenue fell 20% to $1.12 billion in the fourth quarter.

headline: HPE tops Q4 earnings estimates and Q1 guidance expectations
summary: Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE) beat both earnings and revenue estimates in its fiscal fourth quarter, the tech company reporting revenue of $8.46 billion (estimates were for $8.26 billion) and adjusted earnings of $0.58 per share (estimates were for $0.56 per share). Market Domination Overtime hosts Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton sift through the latest earnings release, specifically HPE's fiscal first quarter guidance. Catch Yahoo Finance's interview with HPE CEO Antonio Neri tomorrow, Friday, December 6. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.

headline: American Eagle, Applied Materials, HPE: Top analyst calls
summary: JPMorgan analysts downgrade American Eagle (AEO) to Neutral from Overweight and cut its price target to $23 from $27 after the retailer lowered its revenue outlook, citing weak holiday sales expectations. Applied Materials (AMAT) stock is declining after getting a downgrade to Underweight from Equal Weight from Morgan Stanley due to its outlook for the first half of 2025. Morgan Stanley analysts upgrade Hewlett Packard Enterprise (HPE) to Overweight from Equal Weight with a price target boost to $28 from $23 on enterprise opportunity. Brad Smith and Madison Mills take a closer look at the analyst calls on Morning Brief. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Naomi Buchanan.
